![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/87738f03-d6e0-43f5-81a8-b924388f465a/20240814_173445.jpg?format=original)

HANGMAN PAGE DEF. JAY LETHAL

The match basically starts backstage in the middle of an interview with Jeff Jarrett. Hangman attacks Jay Lethal. They brawl to the ring and then the bell rings. Hangman and Lethal are even until Hangman hits a nasty DVD and shifts the flow of the match.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/9c184b11-b902-45e1-8d5e-b2e143b90211/Screenshot_20240814_174340.jpg?format=original)

PAC says he thought Will Ospreay was his friend until he went behind his back to Tony Khan and took his Wembley moment from him.

So PAC is challenging the winner of MJF vs Will Ospreay to a match at All Out.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/cf5d7e66-45bf-451c-80c2-b58abc6f7f20/Screenshot_20240814_174353.jpg?format=original)

Excellent Darby Allin promo video plays saying nobody would care if Jungle Boy got fired for his antics backstage at All In last year.

Darby is making an entrance when he's attacked by Jungle Boy. They brawl to the back until Jungle Boy drops a garage gate onto Darby’s chest, trapping him.

Jungle Boy tries to break Darby Allin’s neck with a rolling chest but security stops him.

Jungle Boy wants to end Darby at his own game in Wembley Stadium. So he wants a Coffin Match ⚰️

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/df58710a-0b94-4ad1-816f-922687bf58f3/20240814_175518.jpg?format=original)

